spend weekend brunch with me and my honey at one of our favorite restaurants in one of my fave neighborhoods @the_draycott 

located at Palisades village in the Pacific Palisades; a beach community between Malibu and Santa Monica…the Draycott offers American food with British atmosphere (except they actually season the food tho - no shade😭) 

the vibe, aesthetic, and bar looks and feels like London but the menu offerings are seafood, burgers, fish and chips, salad aaaand much more. the menu is easy to digest (pun intended) and not only is this a first choice restaurant but also an easy “if all else fails” place to rely on for food I know I’m going to like no matter what lol

Plus i loooove palisades village for shopping, less tourism, their farmers market, and its overall peaceful, family-friendly vibe. a good handful of designer apparel and beauty stores are in the village too and it’s small enough to visit them all fairly quickly. it’s cute! if you’re ever in town I’d recommend giving it a visit 🤎
